In the end, my time in Haiti was a reminder of the importance of access to healthcare. It is a basic human right, and it is essential for the health and well-being of individuals and communities. If you’re just starting out, it’s best to start small. This will help you test the market and see if your business is viable. Once you’ve established your business, you can then start to grow.
5. Get creative with marketing.
Marketing can be expensive, but there are plenty of ways to market your business on a budget. Social media, word-of-mouth, and content marketing are all effective ways to reach your target market without spending a lot of money.
